Haft ŌĆö the reified free Arrow (`ArrowTerm`) and its interpretation.

Rust source: `deep_causality_haft/src/arrow/arrow_term.rs` (`ArrowCore`, `ArrowVal`, `ArrowCore::interpret`).

Textbook definition. Given a strong category (an Arrow, in the sense of Hughes) the terms freely
generated by a set `G` of generators under the operations `id`, `compose` (`>>>`), `first`,
`second`, `split` (`***`), `fanout` (`&&&`) form the **free arrow** over `G`. As with any free /
initial construction, it carries a universal property: an interpretation of the *generators* into a
target extends **uniquely** to an arrow-homomorphism on the whole term. This is the
initial-algebra-of-a-signature pattern ŌĆö a free term algebra whose universal map is defined by
structural recursion (John Hughes, "Generalising Monads to Arrows," *Sci. Comput. Program.*
37(1ŌĆō3), 2000, for the arrow operations; Steve Awodey, *Category Theory* 2nd ed., ┬¦5, and
J. Goguen, J. Thatcher, E. Wagner, J. Wright, "Initial Algebra Semantics and Continuous Algebras,"
*J. ACM* 24(1), 1977, for free objects / initial-algebra semantics; John C. Reynolds, "Definitional
Interpreters for Higher-Order Programming Languages," ACM Annual Conf. 1972, for the first-order
"erased core" encoding).

This file proves the two facts the Rust reification rests on:
  * `interpret_sound` ŌĆö interpretation is a homomorphism: the interpreter commutes with every
    combinator (`compose` becomes sequencing, `split`/`first`/`second` act componentwise, `fanout`
    copies). This is the precise content of "interpreting a term equals composing its combinators."
  * `free` ŌĆö interpretation is **determined by the generators**: two generator-interpretations that
    agree everywhere induce equal interpretations on every term (the free arrow's universal
    property, proved by structural induction).

DEVIATION NOTES.
  1. Rust has no GADTs, so the object (input/output) types are **erased** in the storable core;
     interpretation therefore runs over one uniform value universe `ArrowVal` ŌĆö a binary tree whose
     `pair` node models the monoidal product the strength combinators act on ŌĆö rather than over
     typed objects. Static well-typedness is recovered on the Rust side by the `ArrowTerm<In,Out,G>`
     fa├¦ade (not modelled here; it adds no equations).
  2. Generators are interpreted as **leaf endomorphisms** `Žå : G ŌåÆ V ŌåÆ V` (a monomorphic target),
     which suffices to state and prove the free-extension property; a fully object-indexed target is
     not needed for these laws.
  3. A combinator applied to a value of the wrong shape (e.g. `first` on a `leaf`) passes the value
     through unchanged ŌĆö unreachable for a term fed its declared input shape, matching the Rust
     fa├¦ade; it only makes `interpret` total.

This file is self-contained (no imports) so it typechecks standalone with bare `lean`.

Rust witness: `deep_causality_haft/tests/formalization_lean/arrow_term_tests.rs`.
-/

namespace DeepCausalityFormal.Haft.ArrowTerm

/-- The erased core: the free arrow over a generator set `G`, as first-order data. Mirrors the Rust
    `ArrowCore<G>` enum. -/
inductive ArrowCore (G : Type) : Type where
  | id
  | gen (g : G)
  | compose (f h : ArrowCore G)
  | first (f : ArrowCore G)
  | second (f : ArrowCore G)
  | split (f h : ArrowCore G)
  | fanout (f h : ArrowCore G)

/-- The value universe interpreted terms flow through ŌĆö a binary tree with payload leaves. Mirrors
    the Rust `ArrowVal<V>`. -/
inductive ArrowVal (V : Type) : Type where
  | leaf (v : V)
  | pair (a b : ArrowVal V)

/-- The interpreter: extend a generator interpretation `Žå` homomorphically over the whole term.
    Mirrors `ArrowCore::interpret` line for line. -/
def interpret {G V : Type} (Žå : G ŌåÆ V ŌåÆ V) : ArrowCore G ŌåÆ ArrowVal V ŌåÆ ArrowVal V
  | .id,          x           => x
  | .gen g,       .leaf v     => .leaf (Žå g v)
  | .gen _,       .pair a b   => .pair a b
  | .compose f h, x           => interpret Žå h (interpret Žå f x)
  | .first _,     .leaf v     => .leaf v
  | .first f,     .pair a b   => .pair (interpret Žå f a) b
  | .second _,    .leaf v     => .leaf v
  | .second f,    .pair a b   => .pair a (interpret Žå f b)
  | .split _ _,   .leaf v     => .leaf v
  | .split f h,   .pair a b   => .pair (interpret Žå f a) (interpret Žå h b)
  | .fanout f h,  x           => .pair (interpret Žå f x) (interpret Žå h x)

variable {G V : Type}

/-- Interpretation is a homomorphism: it commutes with every combinator. `compose` becomes
    sequencing, `first`/`second`/`split` act componentwise on a `pair`, `fanout` copies ŌĆö the exact
    content of "interpreting a term equals composing its combinators." Each equation is definitional.

    THEOREM_MAP: `haft.arrow_term.interpret_sound` -/
theorem interpret_sound (Žå : G ŌåÆ V ŌåÆ V) :
    (ŌłĆ x, interpret Žå .id x = x)
    Ōł¦ (ŌłĆ f h x, interpret Žå (.compose f h) x = interpret Žå h (interpret Žå f x))
    Ōł¦ (ŌłĆ f a b, interpret Žå (.first f) (.pair a b) = .pair (interpret Žå f a) b)
    Ōł¦ (ŌłĆ f a b, interpret Žå (.second f) (.pair a b) = .pair a (interpret Žå f b))
    Ōł¦ (ŌłĆ f h a b,
        interpret Žå (.split f h) (.pair a b) = .pair (interpret Žå f a) (interpret Žå h b))
    Ōł¦ (ŌłĆ f h x, interpret Žå (.fanout f h) x = .pair (interpret Žå f x) (interpret Žå h x)) := by
  refine Ō¤©?_, ?_, ?_, ?_, ?_, ?_Ō¤® <;> intros <;> rfl

/-- The free arrow's universal property: interpretation is **determined by the generators**. If two
    generator-interpretations agree everywhere, they induce equal interpretations on every term.
    Proved by structural induction on the term.

    THEOREM_MAP: `haft.arrow_term.free` -/
theorem free (Žå Žł : G ŌåÆ V ŌåÆ V) (hgen : ŌłĆ g v, Žå g v = Žł g v) :
    ŌłĆ (t : ArrowCore G) (x : ArrowVal V), interpret Žå t x = interpret Žł t x := by
  intro t
  induction t with
  | id => intro x; rfl
  | gen g =>
      intro x
      cases x with
      | leaf v => show ArrowVal.leaf (Žå g v) = ArrowVal.leaf (Žł g v); rw [hgen g v]
      | pair a b => rfl
  | compose f h ihf ihh =>
      intro x
      show interpret Žå h (interpret Žå f x) = interpret Žł h (interpret Žł f x)
      rw [ihf x, ihh (interpret Žł f x)]
  | first f ihf =>
      intro x
      cases x with
      | leaf v => rfl
      | pair a b =>
          show ArrowVal.pair (interpret Žå f a) b = ArrowVal.pair (interpret Žł f a) b
          rw [ihf a]
  | second f ihf =>
      intro x
      cases x with
      | leaf v => rfl
      | pair a b =>
          show ArrowVal.pair a (interpret Žå f b) = ArrowVal.pair a (interpret Žł f b)
          rw [ihf b]
  | split f h ihf ihh =>
      intro x
      cases x with
      | leaf v => rfl
      | pair a b =>
          show ArrowVal.pair (interpret Žå f a) (interpret Žå h b)
              = ArrowVal.pair (interpret Žł f a) (interpret Žł h b)
          rw [ihf a, ihh b]
  | fanout f h ihf ihh =>
      intro x
      show ArrowVal.pair (interpret Žå f x) (interpret Žå h x)
          = ArrowVal.pair (interpret Žł f x) (interpret Žł h x)
      rw [ihf x, ihh x]

end DeepCausalityFormal.Haft.ArrowTerm
